# Deployment Architecture

The following diagram illustrates the deployment architecture for the AI Storytelling RPG, generated based on the Terraform configuration ([terraform/main.tf](file:///Users/tarek/Documents/Obisidian-Vault/Treasure%20Hoard/work/Google%20Agents%20Roloaded/Hackathon/aiagents/terraform/main.tf) and [cloudbuild.tf](file:///Users/tarek/Documents/Obisidian-Vault/Treasure%20Hoard/work/Google%20Agents%20Roloaded/Hackathon/aiagents/terraform/cloudbuild.tf)) and the codebase structure.

## Overview
*   **Infrastructure as Code**: Provisioned using Terraform ([main.tf](file:///Users/tarek/Documents/Obisidian-Vault/Treasure%20Hoard/work/Google%20Agents%20Roloaded/Hackathon/aiagents/terraform/main.tf)).
*   **Hosting Location**: Google Cloud Run hosts all the discrete microservices (Agents, MCP, Frontend).
*   **Databases**: Stateful data is managed by Google Cloud Firestore (Document DB) and Google Cloud Memorystore (Redis).
*   **CI/CD**: Managed by Google Cloud Build, which watches the GitHub repository and pushes Docker images to Google Artifact Registry.

## Architecture Diagram

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    %% Define Styles
    classDef user fill:#f9f9f9,stroke:#333,stroke-width:2px,stroke-dasharray: 5 5
    classDef lb fill:#4285F4,stroke:#fff,color:#fff
    classDef cloudrun fill:#34A853,stroke:#fff,color:#fff
    classDef database fill:#FBBC05,stroke:#fff,color:#333
    classDef build fill:#EA4335,stroke:#fff,color:#fff

    %% External
    User((Player)):::user
    GitHub[GitHub Repository]:::build
    
    %% Load Balancing
    LB[HTTP Load Balancer <br/> lb-backend-1]:::lb
    
    subgraph GCP [Google Cloud Platform]
        %% Frontend
        Frontend[Frontend Web Service <br/> cloud-run-6]:::cloudrun
        
        %% Agents Layer
        subgraph Agents [AI Agent Microservices]
            AgentCW[Agent CreateWorld <br/> cloud-run-2]:::cloudrun
            AgentCC[Agent CreateCharacter <br/> cloud-run-3]:::cloudrun
            AgentNar[Agent Narrative <br/> cloud-run-4]:::cloudrun
            AgentOpt[Agent OptionGen <br/> cloud-run-5]:::cloudrun
        end
        
        %% Central MCP / Backend
        MCPServer[MCP Server / API Backend <br/> cloud-run-1]:::cloudrun
        
        %% Databases
        Firestore[(Firestore DB <br/> Worlds, Chars, Sessions)]:::database
        Redis[(Memorystore Redis)]:::database
        
        %% CI/CD
        CloudBuild[Cloud Build <br/> CI/CD Pipelines]:::build
        ArtifactReg[Artifact Registry <br/> Docker Images]:::build
    end

    %% Connections
    User -->|HTTPS| LB
    LB -->|Routes traffic| Frontend
    
    %% Frontend talks to agents and MCP/Backend
    Frontend -.->|API Calls| MCPServer
    Frontend -.->|Task requests| Agents
    
    %% Agents connect to MCP
    AgentCW -->|Fetches/Saves Data <br/> via fastmcp| MCPServer
    AgentCC -->|Fetches/Saves Data <br/> via fastmcp| MCPServer
    AgentNar -->|Fetches/Saves Data <br/> via fastmcp| MCPServer
    AgentOpt -->|Fetches/Saves Data <br/> via fastmcp| MCPServer
    
    %% MCP connects to DBs
    MCPServer -->|CRUD Operations| Firestore
    MCPServer -->|Cache/State| Redis
    
    %% Build Flow
    GitHub -.->|On Push to main| CloudBuild
    CloudBuild -.->|Build & Push| ArtifactReg
    ArtifactReg -.->|Deploy Image| Agents
    ArtifactReg -.->|Deploy Image| MCPServer
    ArtifactReg -.->|Deploy Image| Frontend
```

### Key Components

1.  **Cloud Run Services**: Each major component is deployed as its own scalable Cloud Run service.
    *   `agent-mcp` (Cloud Run 1): Acts as the central integration point. It exposes tools via the Model Context Protocol (MCP) to the agents and serves core database orchestration.
    *   `agent-createworld` (Cloud Run 2): ADK LlmAgent responsible for world generation.
    *   `agent-createcharacter` (Cloud Run 3): ADK LlmAgent responsible for character validation and portrait generation.
    *   `agent-narrative` (Cloud Run 4): ADK LlmAgent generating the primary story scenes.
    *   `agent-optiongeneration` (Cloud Run 5): ADK LlmAgent generating choices for the user.
    *   `frontend-web` (Cloud Run 6): The user-facing application, placed behind an HTTP load balancer.
2.  **State Management**:
    *   `firestore-1`: The primary persistent document store for Worlds, Characters, and Sessions. Accessed securely by the MCP Server.
    *   `memorystore-1`: A Redis cluster hooked up to the MCP server for fast ephemeral caching or session states.
3.  **Deployment Flow**:
    *   [cloudbuild.tf](file:///Users/tarek/Documents/Obisidian-Vault/Treasure%20Hoard/work/Google%20Agents%20Roloaded/Hackathon/aiagents/terraform/cloudbuild.tf) exposes 2nd-gen GitHub connection triggers.
    *   Pushing to the [main](file:///Users/tarek/Documents/Obisidian-Vault/Treasure%20Hoard/work/Google%20Agents%20Roloaded/Hackathon/aiagents/tools/image_generator/generate_portrait.py#34-64) branch inside specific service folders (`agent-*`) triggers Cloud Build, which builds a Docker container and pushes it to Artifact Registry before Cloud Run pulls the new image.
